  "prompt": "Why am I not able to get a software engineering internship?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're struggling to get a software engineering internship:\n\n1. Technical Skills\n- Insufficient programming knowledge\n- Limited understanding of key languages/frameworks\n- Lack of practical coding experience\n- Not having projects in your portfolio\n\n2. Resume/Application Issues\n- Weak or poorly structured resume\n- Lack of relevant skills/experience\n- Incomplete or generic application\n- Not tailoring applications to specific roles\n\n3. Competition\n- High demand for limited internship positions\n- Competing with many other candidates\n- Strong competition from top universities\n\n4. Networking\n- Limited professional connections\n- Not attending career fairs\n- Not utilizing university career services\n- Not networking on platforms like LinkedIn\n\n5. Interview Preparation\n- Poor technical interview skills\n- Lack of algorithmic/problem-solving practice\n- Inadequate system design knowledge\n- Weak communication during interviews\n\n6. Experience Level\n- No prior internships or relevant experience\n- Limited understanding of industry expectations\n- Not participating in coding competitions/hackathons\n\nRecommendations:\n- Build strong programming skills\n- Create personal coding projects\n- Practice coding challenges\n- Network actively\n- Improve resume and interview skills\n- Consider smaller companies or startups\n\nWould you like specific advice on improving your chances?",
